HEADWORD: overhanded
<hw>overhanded</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>performed with the arm moving
above the shoulder; overhand{2}; -- of methods of throwing, especially
in baseball. Contrasted with <ant>underhand</ant> and
<contr>sidearm</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> overarm.</syn>⟦br⟧
